reviewText: Pretty boring, with cheap production values, poor acting, and a lifeless script. Kathy McKee is STUNNING, however.
Great transfer and very sharp quality for a very rare film!
Absolutely ecstatic and love my purchase over this very, very, *VERY* rare DVD.
I was happy to find this movie on your website because I really wanted to see it but now that I have seen it, I was really disappointed.  The quality of the film and the story line was awful.

Quadroon is an interesting movie. It's the first movie to depict the cruelty and mistreatment of black women during the AnteBellum time. However, the acting should be compared to a junior highschool stage play. This movie doesn't get interesting till end.
